The paper deals with stochastic motion planning in relay networks under a cooperative beamforming framework, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The problem formulation and optimization techniques used in the paper also involve stochastic control (cs.SY) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper proposes a predictive control policy based on expected power reciprocal, which could be related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
